5:
Phew... I'm stuffed. How'd you like the
new item on the menu?
10:
It was delicious. The potatoes were
amazing...
14:
Good to hear. How about you,
Pharah? I hope it suited your palate.
23:
...Mm, yeah. It was good. A little
sweet for me, though.
28:
Ah, I see. People from different
places have got different tastes. It's
tough to make something everyone
will like...
32: Oh, no, I'm not trying to whine. Sorry.
38: How long have I been here?
41:
There's no wind or dust... Nobody's
trying to kill me in my sleep...
44:
This is basically an utopian life...
Wouldn't you agree, Hellcat of the
Dunes?
48:
Hey... I've been looking for you. Why'd
you call for me?
52:
...I'm going to get soft if I keep this up
any longer.
56: Hang out with me for a little bit.
75:
...The hell? Why so quiet? Break this
weird tension and say something.
79: The Cobra, right? I remember now.
83:
Popsâ€”I mean, the Cobra? You knew
him?
87:
Never met the guy, but he was well
known where I was at. Part of one of
the biggest bandit gangs in the
borderlands.
90:
...Pops, huh? He wasn't your dad, was
he?
94: Huh... The look in your eyes changed.
99:
Damn cat... You shouldn't have said
that.
104:
*pant* Y-you... Are you playing with
me?
107:
You b-bastard... you're going... easy
on me!
111:
...Oh, cut the crap. If YOU were going
all out, wouldn't you be using that
poison of yours?
117:
Maybe it's time you showed me who
you really are?
125:
Look at me... laughing like this. When
I'm with you guys... I'm pathetic.
128:
Here, this should cover the cost of
lodging. I'm going back now, so
thanks for your hospitality.
131:
Get out of my way. My next
destination's my decision to make.
135:
Then I'm coming with you. That's my
decision to make.
139:
...What? What do you want? Why do
you care about where I go?
143:
...Because I'd be sad to see you
leave.
147:
...Haha. What am I even supposed to
say here?
150: Even after all this time, I...
160: O-oh, it's you... Sorry about earlier.
169: ...Yeah, I am. I just can't relax here.
172:
...Cobra. That's the name of a thief
who became a sort of parent for me.
175:
This place is exactly the sort of
utopia that the old man was always
dreaming about. Maybe that's why
it's hard for me to feel at home here...
179: Is the Cobra not around anymore?
183:
Hahaha... Not anymore, no. He was a
big softie who was always helping
people out, until someone caught
him flat-footed one day.
185:
...This all happened in the distant
past... Somewhere in the sandstorm
that raged under yesterday's sun.
199:
It was a very nice smile. The kind I'm
familiar with.
203:
Hah...Hahaha! A nice smile, eh?
You're really out there, girl. You know
that?
206: You kinda remind me of Pops...
209:
I-I'm going back to bed! I want to be
alone for a bit...
221:
I still can't remember what you told
me back then...
